We recommended to the management the following actions:

 1.Create a clear process flow with detailed timelines for the grant of Capital Assistance;
 2.Establish the “Other receivables” account for grants that were not yet liquidated and ensure that succeeding transactions will be debited to “Other receivables;”
 Revise the livelihood agreement to include the necessary details such as dates, timelines, amount of the grant, needed documents for liquidation of the clients, penalty clause for non-compliance, and other necessary stipulation to safeguard the interest of the LGU;
3.Avoid erasures in the agreement as much as possible. Otherwise, ensure that all erasures and alterations are countersigned and acknowledged by the parties of the agreement; 
4.Require written letter-requests from the clients to support the grant of financial assistance; 
 Issue notices to clients who have yet to liquidate their claims; and
5.Maintain file copies of the livelihood project monitoring reports and attach the same along with their corresponding liquidation reports to support the Journal Entry Vouchers for liquidation.

